itiative leverages shared engineering resources, intellectual property, and infrastructure across Tesla and SpaceX, along with Intel’s expertise in designing, fabricating, and packaging ultra-high-performance chips at scale.\n* **Orbital AI:** Terafab directly enables planned orders-of-magnitude increases in AI compute deployment in orbit, which would otherwise be constrained by pure reliance on external foundries. The company expects significant speed and cost advantages from Terafab’s vertical integration, providing a critical competitive advantage in the race to scale AI infrastructure.\n* **Complementary to Third-Party Suppliers:** While Terafab is intended to expand internal chip manufacturing capabilities, the company expects to continue sourcing a significant portion of its compute hardware from third-party suppliers, viewing Terafab as complementary to these relationships.\n\n#### **Forward-Looking Statements and Disclaimers**\nThe text includes specific disclaimers regarding the uncertainties and early-stage nature of the Terafab project:\n\n* **Lack of Definitive Agreements:** "In connection with such collaboration, we have agreed with Tesla on a general framework for the future development of Terafab. Any specific projects undertaken pursuant to this framework will be subject to separate negotiations and agreements (including any development timelines, milestones and capital expenditures) and have not yet been determined."\n* **Early-Stage Uncertainty:** "Certain of these projects, including Macrohard and Terafab, are in the very early stages, as a result of which we and Tesla have not finalized a variety of details relating to our collaboration, including, but not limited to, financial terms, intellectual property rights, and the ultimate term of our collaboration."\n* **No Assurance of Success or Partner Commitment:** "While Terafab is intended to expand our internal chip manufacturing capabilities and alleviate potential future AI chip shortages at SpaceX... there can be no assurance that we will be able to achieve our objectives with respect to Terafab within the expected timeframes, or at all. While we have a framework agreement with Tesla, neither Tesla nor Intel are obligated to remain a part of the project, and we may not enter into any such definitive agreements."',
